[SECURITY] TOTP enrollment confirm failed

A TOTP enrollment attempt failed at the confirmation step — the
authenticator code did not match the server-side secret. Usually a
clock-skew issue or a wrong QR scan.

  Event  : {{ event_type }}
  When   : {{ when_str }}
  IP     : {{ ip or '(unknown)' }}
  Agent  : {{ user_agent or '(none)' }}
  Reason : {{ extra or '(none)' }}

Repeated failures from one IP are suspicious — a successful enroll
would bind an authenticator under attacker control.

What to do:
  1. If you weren't enrolling, re-run totp/enroll yourself to overwrite
     the pending secret.
  2. If the failure was you on a new device, re-scan the fresh QR.
